      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Benzenediazonium carboxylate decomposes when heated to yield N<sub>2</sub>, CO<sub>2</sub>, and a reactive substance that can’t be isolated. When benzene-diazonium carboxylate is heated in the presence of furan, the following reaction is observed:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbWdWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--8904ba8bbb96391cc1787f3591c46ba8773e298b/OChem_16_EC_026.jpg\" alt=\"When heated, benzenediazonium carboxylate reacts with furan to yield an organic product, carbon dioxide, and nitrogen.\">\n<p>What intermediate is involved in this reaction? Propose a mechanism for its formation.</p>",
